      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Minimum wage increases can be a mixed bag for small businesses like yours. On one hand, higher wages can lead to increased consumer spending power, potentially boosting your sales. On the other hand, the increased labor costs can put a strain on your budget, especially in a low-cost living area. It's a delicate balance, but many small businesses adapt by optimizing operations, increasing prices, or finding efficiencies elsewhere.",
